solutions.content:
**Logic :** 
Every node have two choices : 
- Follow the parent direction what his parent want
- Don't follow the parent given direction and go reverse direction (may be find longest path)

Then update the `max ` accordingly `parent_direction_longest_length` and `child_own_direction_longest_length`.

```
class Solution {
    int max = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

    public int longestZigZag(TreeNode root) {
        solve(root, false);
        solve(root, true);
        return max;
    }

    // Right direction -> dir = true
    // Left direction -> dir = false
    public int solve(TreeNode node, boolean dir) {
        if (node == null) return -1;

        // if we go right dir from node
        int right = ((node.right == null) ? -1 : solve(node.right, false)) + 1;

        // if we go left dir from node
        int left = ((node.left == null) ? -1 : solve(node.left, true)) + 1;

        // if child is not serious about parent direction
        // He want to go own direction for check longest path (reverse of given parent direction)
        int childDirProfit = (dir) ? left : right;
        // if coming from right go left and vice versa for parent
        int parentDirProfit = (dir) ? right : left; 

        // update the max
        max = Math.max(max, Math.max(childDirProfit, parentDirProfit));

        // return what parent wanted
        return parentDirProfit;
    }
}
```
It's a simple DFS Solution so it will take `O(n)` times.
n = number of node in Tree.


