1. If the current node is a left child, 
    - `dfs(node->right,currLen+1)` to continue the ZigZag path
    - `dfs(node->left,1)`- Start a new ZigZag path from current node (left direction)
2. If the current node is a right child,
    - `dfs(node->left,currLen+1)` to continue the ZigZag path
    - `dfs(node->right,1)` - Start a new ZigZag path from current node (right direction)

So we can do a DFS traversal from root in both directions and at each node update the maximum length of the path (edges in the path).

