# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Intuition 1 - We will do post order traversal as we want to use the results of the children stored in a DP natured map data structure.

Intuition 2 - We will use 2 persistent variables namely a dp map and a MAX variable. that signify the following:
1. ***DP map*** -> Will store an int array of size 2 consisting of the max zigzag length if you start from this root in both left and right direction. Index 0 holds the left scenario and 1 holds the right scenario.
2. ***MAX*** -> used to calculate max length seen so far.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
After every postorder computation DP will hold <Key, Value> as <Current Node reference, Array[max distance from here if you go left, max distance from here if you go right]>

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n) where n is the number of nodes as we go over every node just once
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n) as dp is the size of nodes as keys and values are constant of size 2
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    int MAX;
    Map<TreeNode, int []> dp;
    public int longestZigZag(TreeNode root) {

        //postorder traversal
        //Map stores left from node and right from node
        dp = new HashMap<>();
        dfs(root);
        return MAX;
    }

    //returns max length from here if you go in a particular direction
    private void dfs(TreeNode root){
        if(root == null) return;

        if(root.left == null && root.right == null){
            dp.put(root, new int[]{0,0});
            return;
        }
        //In dp value int []
        //index 0 represents left direction
        //index 1 represents right direction
        dfs(root.left);
        dfs(root.right);

        int left = 0, right = 0;

        if(dp.get(root.left) != null)
            left = 1 + dp.get(root.left)[1]; //we go right after left

        if(dp.get(root.right) != null)
            right = 1 + dp.get(root.right)[0]; //we go left after right
        dp.put(root, new int[]{left, right});
        MAX = Math.max(MAX, Math.max(left,right));
    }
}

```

