solutions.content:
Theory:

1. Longest zigzag path can either begin from "left" or "right" edge. Hence need to find max from these two.
2. When we are at root, we will start by saying that, we have taken hypothetical path "l" or "r" with length 0.
3. when we are at left node, we check whether the prev edge we took is "r". If yes increase the path length. else we need to start new journey from here because Left - > Left is not zigzag.
4. Similarly when we are at right node we check if the prev edge we took is "l". If yes, our zigzag path will increase by one. If not, then new journey will start from here because Right -> Right path is not zigzag. 

```
var longestZigZag = function(root) {
    let max = 0;

    const helper = (node, prev, length) => {

        if(node === null)
            return null;

        max = Math.max(max, length);

        helper(node.left, "l" , prev === "r" ? length + 1 : 1);
        helper(node.right, "r" , prev === "l" ? length + 1 : 1);
    }


    helper(root, "l", 0); 
    helper(root, "r", 0);

    return max;
};
```

