solutions.content:
I am using a deque for BFS in python.
The node of the BFS will be **{curr_node, state(can be 'L' or 'R'), longestdistance}** where longest distance = longest zigzag distance so far.

Now if your current state is 'L' and a right child exist for the current node, we will extend the current longest distance by 1 (same case for state 'R' and existence of a left child)

```
